description.narrative: The public awareness of children's issues in the Middle East and North Africa (MENA) increased through a number of multi-sectoral milestones, helping to paint a comprehensive regional picture on what it means to grow up as a child in a region impacted by poverty, deprivation and armed conflict. While focus continues to be on partnerships with the media, UNICEF expanded the circle of audiences through the digital transformation project and public outreach. Work is ongoing to create more tangible impact through engagement with the public to promote positive change for children and highlight the impact of conflict on children. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:20/02/2020
